Text.SourceString: Hello! I don’t think I’ve seen you before. Are you new in town?
See you around!
We’re open every day… Weather permitting, that is.

What a beautiful day to be outdoors.//I think I might go to Garden Lane before work tomorrow to enjoy my morning beverage and look at the butterflies. Hmm…//<portrait=happy>No, yeah… I will definitely do that.
I’m not too worried about how much the coffee shop makes. Creating the perfect cup of coffee is where my mind is.//Each individual cup… Yeah, each of them is special.
I can’t stand when people wear perfume that’s too strong…//It overwhelms my nose for the day, and I don’t like that.//I like to be able to smell the coffee.
Vegetables? As in <Italic>raw</> vegetables?//None for me, thanks. I’m not big on vegetables. Fruit, on the other hand…
Now, now… It doesn’t mean I don’t eat my vegetables, ’cause I do.//I do! Seriously!//I just don’t do it for fun…or have more than the recommended amount.
The coffee maker at the shop is weather resistant.//It can withstand rain – snow even!//It was costly…but worth every penny.
My hair gets sticky fast in Summer. Kinda hate it… Is yours that way too?
The beach isn’t the place to sell coffee. Not freshly brewed, anyway. In cans, yeah, maybe! //<portrait=sad>At the beach, with the unpredictable wind blowing sand around… Yeah, no.
For Spring, I usually go for a coffee with floral notes. It seems fitting for the season.
The coffee shop opened as usual in Winter.//But we closed when it got too cold. Thankfully, those days are behind us now.

Coffee beans from different regions taste different. Things like soil and weather have an impact.//Correct me if I’m wrong, but I don’t think you can grow <Italic>good</> coffee beans right now, right? In Spring?
Not at all, huh? Yeah, that sounds about right.//I didn’t think you could grow coffee here in Spring, not in this weather. No…yeah.
Will you be planting coffee this Summer?
So, are you the type of person who drinks hot coffee in Summer?
That’s what I’m talking about!
I prefer to brew locally grown beans, of course…but yeah, no. There isn’t much choice, unfortunately.//We can only plant coffee here in Summer. So that means I have to import some of my beans.
I don’t drink coffee every day. Yeah…no.//I do enjoy the many different flavors each cup offers. Always a great experience… A mood booster.
I think Summer is perfect for coffee with citrus notes. Doesn’t Summer feel like a citrusy season to you?

I pay attention to my customers when it comes to when they prefer to have their coffee, and of course, their favorite blend.// For instance, the astrophysicist, <NPCName>Wakuu</>, likes his coffee in the afternoon, and <NPCName>Aaliyah</> likes it early in the morning.//Yeah, she’s the military pilot. Was or is – not sure.
Have you seen the daisies? I’m so tempted to put some in my beard!
There’s something about drinking hot chocolate in Fall, isn’t there?//Something special about it…
Every once in a while, I create a coffee omakase, usually in Fall.//I taste-test my favorite combos of the year before putting them on the menu.
For Fall, you just gotta go with the classic cocoa and caramel notes in your coffee. It’s perfect for this season.
Have you ever tried cooking with dragon fruit, friend? It looks so dramatic, doesn’t it?//<portrait=annoyed>I’ve been trying to come up with a recipe for it, but I haven’t come up with anything good.
Being outdoors has its downside on days like this…
A warm drink for the day?
Some people are immune to Winter, it seems.//Saw <NPCName>Macy</> walking around in shorts the other day.//<portrait=happy>I was shocked… Impressed in a way, but yeah, no. I can’t do that. Ha ha!
I don’t wear perfume or anything that’s strongly scented…especially when I’m making coffee or blending beans.//Those scents can get into the coffee beans.
The inn gets really cold in Winter.//<portrait=happy>Thank goodness for portable heaters.
Living at the inn is great, especially in Winter. It’s cold, and you just wanna hang out with friends.//Yeah, the inn is cold, and the heater is…questionable at times, but the residents are friendly.
This here is my coffee shop. Stop by whenever you feel the need for that jolt of caffeine!
I like the way I look now, and I’m comfortable with myself, but there was a time when I felt like I had to fit into certain boxes to appeal to others.
Some people can be very… gatekeepy. Even those who claim to be open-minded.

I didn’t grow up drinking coffee. My family was more of a tea family. But I just find coffee more interesting, you know?//<portrait=happy>The taste, the brewing process, the roasting process, even how it’s grown and harvested is much more interesting to me than tea.
I don’t like a lot of fuss for my morning coffee, so I’ll usually go for a French press.//Later in the day, I can go for something more complex, like a pour-over or an espresso.

Oh, a good grinder is a must if you want delicious coffee. The really good ones can cost hundreds and thousands of coins.//<portrait=normal>For home use, just avoid using those blade grinders and stick to burr grinders. The hand-cranked ones are pretty good and not too expensive.
Or – here’s an idea!//You can just stop by my coffee shop and skip all the hassle, yeah?
As much as I love coffee, I also want to sell and consume it sustainably. Buy locally and all that.//<portrait=normal>Speaking of, do you grow coffee, and if so, can I buy some from you?
I named my coffee shop after me. After my full name.//<portrait=normal>Ha ha! No…yeah. Truth! My full name is Raja.
It means “King.” No…yeah, seriously.
Ha! That caught me off guard.//<portrait=normal>Thank you for the kind words.
The other time, you asked me if my name had any meaning… What about you, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//What does <PlayerName>$Player</> mean?
Well, you suit the name.//<PlayerName>$Player</> is so you.
Just like you… What a personality.
Ah, so that’s not your given name.//<portrait=normal>It fits you. <PlayerName>$Player</> is a lovely name.

Special.SourceString: Well, I picked it because I liked the way it sounds.

Text.SourceString: The coffee shop is closed when it rains like this. So I usually spend the day volunteering at the shelter.
Out in the rain? Got a place to be?
The coffee shop is closed when it rains like this. So I usually spend the day volunteering at the shelter.
Out in the rain this late? Got someplace to be?
The coffee shop is closed when it storms like this. So I usually spend the day volunteering at the shelter.
Out in the storm? Got someplace to be?
You’re out late today, in the storm too.//<portrait=happy>Busy as usual, yeah? Nothing can slow you down.
Busy as usual, yeah? No snow can slow you down.
Maybe I’ll wear a hat next time. This snow gets my hair all wet.
Do you like dinner parties, friend?//<portrait=normal>I can’t think of a better way to spend a cold night like this. Fine coffee, delicious food, warm <Italic>convos</>… Hmm…
The ladies at the inn – the twins, yeah? They let me decorate my room the way I want.//They’re very generous.
They provide extra blankets too.//<portrait=annoyed>Not that we need them, though… In this heat? Yeah, no!

The ladies at the inn are always so adventurous with their sheets. On a Winter day like this not too long ago, I came home to tie-dyed sheets!//<portrait=happy>That was certainly <Italic>something</>.
<PlayerName>$player</>, what sorts of things do you like to do when you’re not working?
Oh yeah? Are you good at it?//Pool’s one of those things I’d like to get better at, but I haven’t worked at it.
Ahh. Of course… You strike me as the beach type.//<portrait=normal>Good taste. I, myself, prefer the garden, but who can resist the beach?

Whew, is it hot or was my coffee too strong? Good gosh, it’s hot! I am <Italic>so</> wired today!//I tried out a new coffee blend, and it hit way harder than I expected!//Don’t-think-I’ve-blinked-in-the-past-five-minutes!-Whew!
I’m-talking-really-fast!//I need to sit down.
I love people watching, so owning the coffee stand really is the best job for me.//<portrait=normal>I get to stand here all day and see people go by.
Yeah, I get sore feet at the end of the day, but people are interesting… It’s worth it.
When it’s humid, we expect angry clouds.//Beauty never arrives alone… There’s always a price attached.

There’s no such thing as weather that’s too hot for drinking hot beverages.//<portrait=annoyed>Drinking coffee is an <Italic>experience</>. You can’t just put <Italic>ice</> in it.//No! Ice waters down the flavor.

I’m not one for seasonal drinks. I like a variety of coffee beans, but I don’t think I could bring myself to drink any of the stranger concoctions, like pumpkin lattes.//<portrait=annoyed>Yeah…no. The thing is, I don’t think a lot of that stuff tastes good, when it comes to it.
I also don’t like jamu, if that’s any indication.//<portrait=happy>What are we even talking about?
Since I can’t open my stand today, I figured I’d come down to the community center and see what’s going on.
It’s hard to farm in the rain too, huh?//<portrait=happy>We can be bad-weather buddies!
I think I should get some dog biscuits to keep on the counter.//<portrait=normal>So if people bring their dogs, they can have a treat too.
I saw Taco playing around the other day, enjoying the sunny Spring day in the fountain.//<portrait=happy>He sure knows how to have fun!
Oh gosh! I sure hope Taco was actually playing in that fountain and not…//Oh good gosh!
Is it too early to bust out my swimming trunks?//<portrait=normal>Ah, yeah… I can wait till Summer.

This place needs a good coffee shop.//It’s a complete waste to drink bad coffee. There’s only so many drinks you can have in a lifetime.//<portrait=sad>Ah, very limited. I pity anybody who doesn’t have access to a good brew.
It’s way too snowy to open the coffee stand.//<portrait=normal>Better stay in close to the fireplace.
When the snow stops, we can open the coffee shop again, but not now, not today.//Today we relax and give back.
I want to do something fun this Summer.//<portrait=normal>I’m thinking beach day every day!
That’s what Summer is for!
<Italic>Iced coffee?</> What do you mean iced coffee?//Yeah, no… We don’t do iced coffee.
Have you seen the cats? Where are those cats?//<portrait=annoyed>The orange one! I think the orange cat kicked over a whole sack of beans yesterday!

I know what I saw, okay? The other day, I saw that cat and the other one playing around with the sack of beans.//<portrait=angry>Tried to <Italic>shoo</> it nicely, but obviously, it didn’t work. I came in and there were beans all over the floor!
I can’t rely on shipping by sea here.//<portrait=angry>I ordered some coffee beans from San Franciskyo. They were supposed to be here by now, but no cargo boats are coming until next week.
What am I supposed to do? I heard <NpcName>Ben</> can get you the good stuff, even rare finds, but he doesn’t travel much anymore.//I can’t run my business based on <NpcName>Ben’s</> moods.
Coffee is the perfect drink for people-watching.//It’s a great excuse to sit and observe all the interesting things that are going on.
That’s how I fell in love with it – coffee.//<portrait=normal>Well, and people-watching.
I’ve always loved the idea of running my own coffee shop, and now I get to do it here, where I can really get to know my customers.
I’ve met interesting folks here…through coffee.//<portrait=happy>A hunter, some scientists, a new farmer escaping the city life. *winks*
I knew I’d enjoy living in an inn. I enjoy any kind of shared living arrangement.
I meet so many interesting people here. One of the tenants has a pet lobster.//<portrait=concerned>A lobster, yeah. You don’t see that every day…
Good thing I found this place. Renting one room is much cheaper than renting a whole house.
Plus, I think I’d get really lonely if I lived in a house all by myself.//<portrait=sad>My fire would go out so fast…

Let’s be real. We all picked Coral Island partly because it was once such a lively place.//<portrait=sad>All the tourists… The business potential was on another level. Until the oil spill took it all away. *sighs*
Well, I guess not for you. It was your family’s farm you moved to, wasn’t it?//<portrait=happy>I guess you’re pretty much local.
I owe the twins a lot – not financially…//<portrait=sad>Well, sometimes financially… They’re lenient about the rent, and I’m thankful for that.

It isn’t exactly raining money at the coffee shop right now. And gosh, the expenses don’t quit. Rent, beans, staff, <Italic>my</> rent. Gosh!//<portrait=sad>Running the shop is so expensive, sometimes I think about giving it up…
I feel for the people here – before the Coffee Corner arrived. They had to go so far to get a <Italic>good</> cup of coffee.
It reminds me of my days in San Franciskyo. Not the bad coffee – the opposite, actually.//<portrait=happy>That place had so many good shops. I never had to walk more than thirty minutes to find one.
Rent for my shop in Starlet Town is cheap.//<portrait=sad>So number-wise, it should have been a low-risk move to start my business here. You’d think, right? But nope.
Sales here aren’t too <Italic>hot</>.//<portrait=sad>Even covering the relatively cheap rent is a struggle sometimes…
I must admit starting a business wasn’t as easy as I thought.//<portrait=concerned>Gotta miss the times when all I had to worry about was making coffee…being a barista.
You gotta look in the mirror in the morning and like what you see. That’s what <Italic>living</> is all about.//Wear something that makes you feel good. Every day is a new day.
I put effort into what I wear every day. Yes, I do.//<portrait=happy>So what if we have nowhere to go? We gotta be happy with ourselves <Italic>for</> ourselves. Look good, feel good, right?

Silk clothing is good for this weather. Super breathable, good for your skin.//Gotta make sure your skin – your body – can breathe.//<portrait=happy>A silk pillowcase is a good idea too. It’s good for your hair.

Silk clothing is good for this weather. Super breathable, good for your skin.//Gotta make sure your skin – your body – can breathe in this heat.//<portrait=happy>A silk pillowcase is a good idea too. It’s good for your hair.

When I get myself new outfit, yeah, it isn’t cheap, but the way I see it is this is what I wear.//This is how my body will feel for a lot of hours in the day, and you gotta consider that to be a priority, right?
I don’t know where you got that outfit, but it looks great on you.//<portrait=happy>Good quality fabric, I can tell… Looks warm as heck. Is it a wool blend?
I don’t know where you got that outfit, but it looks great on you.//<portrait=happy>Good quality fabric, I can tell. Nice. Very <Italic>summery</>.
The White Flamingo has this shirt I want, but it’s way too expensive.//Maybe I’ll save up for it.
